🚨 BIG PROBLEM WITH THIS CODE
const UserContext = () => {
  const UserContext = createContext();
}

❌ Problem 1:

👉 Every render-ku new context create aagum

📌 Result:

*Provider & Consumer match aagaadhu
*App break aagum

❌ Problem 2:

👉 Naming clash 😵

const UserContext = () => {
  const UserContext = createContext();
}


*Same name function & variable ❌
*Confusion + error


❌ Problem 3:

👉 JSX return thevai illa

*Context UI illa
*<div></div> waste

----------------------------------------------------

✅ CORRECT WAY (WHY THIS IS RIGHT)

import { createContext } from "react";

const UserContext = createContext();

export default UserContext;



